        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 9:25PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 925 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Lum to near Capac to
near Armada. Movement was northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Richmond, Capac, Memphis, and Emmett around 930 PM EDT.
Yale around 940 PM EDT.
Brown City and Melvin around 945 PM EDT.
Lakeport around 1005 PM EDT.
Port Huron and Marysville around 1010 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include North Street,
Goodland Township, Birch Beach, Lynn Township, Rattle Run, Amador,
Goodells, Brockway, Smiths Creek, and Valley Center.

People attending Armada Fair should seek safe shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
